"title": "5614: weights and measures, laws concerning",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5614: weights and measures, laws concerning",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God expects his people to use accurate weights and measures, and to use just balances. This is underlined in the Law, the Prophets and the wisdom literature.</p>\n<h2>The law demanded honesty in using weights and measures</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:35-Lev19:36\">LEV 19:35–19:36</a></strong> <em>Cheating by falsifying weights and measures was common in a culture where there was no standardisation or regulatory authority.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13-Deut25:16\">DEU 25:13–25:16</a></p>\n<h2>The prophets called for the right use of weights and measures</h2>\n<h3>A call for honesty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:9-Ezek45:10\">EZK 45:9–45:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Condemnation of dishonesty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:4-Amos8:6\">AMO 8:4–8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:7-Hos12:8\">HOS 12:7–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:10-Mic6:14\">MIC 6:10–6:14</a></p>\n<h2>Instruction from Proverbs on weights and measures</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:10\">PRO 20:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a> <em>Merchants carried stones of different sizes in a pouch for weighing silver for payment</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:28\">PRO 22:28</a> <em>To move a boundary stone was in effect to steal land.</em></p>",
